<TITLE>Statement by the Director General Hans Blix on his appointment for a fourth term</TITLE>
<H3 ALIGN=CENTER>Statement by the Director General Hans Blix on his appointment for a fourth term</H3>
<H4 ALIGN=CENTER>Appointment for a fourth term</H4>
<P><H4 ALIGN=CENTER>Vienna, Austria</H4>
<P><H4 ALIGN=CENTER>28 September 1993</H4>
<P><HR><H4 ALIGN=CENTER>Mr. President,</H4>
<P>I should like to thank the General Conference for the confidence it is showing in me by approving my appointment as Director General for a fourth term.  I am very happy that my service during the nearly twelve years that I have been here has been such that the Board and the General Conference have wanted to prolong my mandate.
<P>The years that lie immediately ahead of us are likely to be full of exciting challenges and I feel grateful for the opportunity to work with Member Governments and with a highly competent Secretariat to meet these challenges.  Nuclear disarmament and arms control measures will drastically reduce the number of nuclear weapons, but may also call for verification activities by the IAEA.  The non-proliferation regime may reach universality.  There is a large agenda - with a role for the IAEA - before the 1995 NPT Conference.  There is another large agenda for the strengthening of nuclear power safety, to make nuclear power an even more important part - and a more accepted part - of a global sustainable energy production.  And there is yet another large agenda for the transfer of nuclear techniques in medicine, agriculture and industry to promote development.
<P>The IAEA is a good organization to work in.  Member Governments and policy-making organs have a long tradition of defining joint interests and translating them into constructive action.  Although inevitably politics are never far away, the organization's dedication to science, technology and rationality is a great asset.  An engaged, professionally highly competent, international staff is a third asset.
<P>Mr. President, I am proud to be given the confidence to head this Secretariat for a fourth term and I assure you that I shall serve all the Member States enthusiastically and impartially.
<HR>
</BODY>
</HTML>
