STI/PUB/66/SPI/9 (460 pp., 124 figures; 1983)
<BR>
ISBN 92-0-149083-6
<BR>
Price: 900 Austrian Schillings
<P>
<B>
The Chemical Thermodynamics of Actinide Elements and Compounds
</B>
<P>
This series originally consisted of 10 parts, of which 6 are
still available, comprising a critical assessment of the chemical
thermodynamic properties of the actinide elements and compounds.
Each part is devoted to an individual class of actinide compound,
and the text gives the thermodynamic characterization in the low-
and high-temperature regions as well as the properties of the
gaseous state and the vaporization behaviour. For most actinide
materials, thermodynamic data over the complete temperature range
are also included in tabular form.
<P>
<B>
Part 4: The Actinide Chalcogenides
</B>
<P>
<I>Contents:</I> General information; Introduction; Thorium
chalcogenides; Protactinium chalcogenides; Uranium chalcogenides;
Neptunium chalcogenides; Plutonium chalcogenides; Transplutonium
chalcogenides; Thermodynamic properties of the actinide
chalcogenides; Heat-capacity contributions from a population of
excited electronic states in the actinides; References;
Appendices: Tables of thermodynamic functions.
<P>
STI/PUB/424/04 (265 pp., 47 figures; 1984)
<BR>
ISBN 92-0-149084-4
<BR>
Price: 660 Austrian Schillings
<P>
