ISBN 92-0-145083-4<BR>
Price: 860 Austrian Schillings
<P>
<B>Isotope Hydrology 1983<BR>
<I>Proceedings Series</I></B>
<P>
Proceedings of a symposium organized in co-operation with UNESCO,
Vienna, 12-16 September 1983. Isotope techniques are in their
third decade of application to hydrological investigations and
have reached full maturity as scientific and practical tools.
However, these proceedings demonstrate that new ideas continue to
develop.
<P>
<I>Contents:</I> Environmental isotopes in precipitation and
surface water studies; Studies in the unsaturated zone; Field
studies of groundwater dynamics with environmental isotopes;
Groundwater age determination and related problems; Groundwater
pollution studies; Artificial isotope applications; Poster
presentations.
<P>
