<BODY BGCOLOR=#ffffff>
<CENTER>
<H2>
Nuclear and Radiological Safety
</H2>
</CENTER>
<P>
<CENTER>
<A HREF=/worldatom/publications/96pubs/96nrs.html><IMG BORDER=0
SRC=/worldatom/publications/grafix/new.gif align=center></A>
</center>
<p>
<CENTER>
<I>
To view the latest <B>1996 publications</B> for this section, click the
above icon.</I>
</CENTER>
<P>
<HR>
<P>
<B>
Nuclear Safety Review 1995
<BR>
Part D of the IAEA Yearbook 1995
</B>
<P>
A new format has been adopted for the Nuclear Safety Review 1995.
The focus of the report has been shifted to feature a number of
prominent relevant issues and to concentrate on their
implications for radiation and nuclear safety.  It includes
in-depth discussions of steam generator integrity, control rod
drive nozzle cracking, fire protection, childhood cancers near
nuclear installations and radon induced health effects.  Related
IAEA activities such as the feedback of operating experience
based on the IAEA event reporting and operational safety services
are also addressed.
<P>
<I>Contents:</I>  Highlights;  Nuclear safety - topical issues; 
Radiation safety - topical issues;  International safety
activities. 
<P>
STI/PUB/988 (75 pp., 20 figures, 18 x 24 cm;  1995)
<BR>
ISBN 92-0-101495-3
<BR>
Price:  140 Austrian Schillings
<P>
