<B>
Manpower Requirements and Development for Nuclear Power
Programmes
<BR>
<I>Proceedings Series</I>
</B>
<P>
Proceedings of a symposium, Saclay, France, 2-6 April 1979. The
promotion of manpower development in the nuclear field, a
demanding technology, requires excellence in human performance.
The availability of adequately qualified manpower is an essential
condition of success of any nuclear power programme or project as
well as of transfer of technology. This is especially relevant
for the developing countries. The papers deal with the whole
range of this subject and discuss both general and specific
aspects of manpower requirements and development, referring to
national experience as well as discussing specifically
international assistance in training.
<P>
<I>Contents:</I> General aspects of manpower requirements and
development; National experience and manpower development
programmes; International assistance in training; Specific fields
and aspects of manpower development; Panel discussion. 
