NUSS Programme
<P>
QUALITY ASSURANCE
</H3>
</CENTER>
<p>
<HR>
<P>
<B>
<A NAME=83>Code on the Safety of Nuclear Power Plants: Quality 
Assurance 
<BR>
<I>Safety Series No. 50-C-QA (Rev. 1)</I></A>
</B>
<P>
Principles and objectives for establishment and implementation of
quality assurance programmes applied to both the overall and each
of the constituent activities associated with a nuclear power
plant or nuclear facility. Encompasses the activities necessary:
(a) to achieve the appropriate quality of the respective item or
service; and (b) to verify that the required quality is achieved
and objective evidence is produced.
<P>
<I>Contents:</I> Definitions; 1. Introduction; 2. Quality
assurance programmes; 3. Organization; 4. Document control; 5.
Design control; 6. Procurement control; 7. Control of items; 8.
Process control; 9. Inspection and test control; 10.
Non-conformance control; 11. Corrective actions; 12. Records; 13.
Audits.
<P>
STI/PUB/800 (34 pp.; 1988)
<BR>
E ISBN 92-0-123688-3
<BR>
C ISBN 92-0-523490-7
<BR>
F ISBN 92-0-223589-9
<BR>
R ISBN 92-0-423890-9
<BR>
S ISBN 92-0-323589-2
<BR>
Price: 130 Austrian Schillings
