<B>
<A NAME=86>Quality Assurance in the Procurement of Items and
Services for
Nuclear Power Plants: A Safety Guide
<BR>
<I>Safety Series No. 50-SG-QA3</I></A>
</B>
<P>
Requirements and recommendations related to the establishment,
implementation and administration of procurement activities.
Comprises supply of items (including spare and replacement
parts) and services, or a combination thereof, during the stages
of the design, manufacture, construction, commissioning and
operation of a nuclear power plant. Applicable to the responsible
organization, plant designers, architect-engineers, suppliers,
plant constructors, plant operators and other participating
organizations. 
<P>
<I>Contents:</I> Introduction; Planning for procurement;
Procurement document preparation, review, distribution and change
control; Selection of suppliers of items and services; Bid
evaluation and award of contract; Purchaser evaluation of
supplier performance; Verification activities by purchaser;
Non-conformance control and corrective actions; Acceptance of
item or service; Quality assurance records; Audit of procurement
programme.
