<B>
<A NAME=89>Quality Assurance in the Design of Nuclear Power
Plants: A Safety
Guide
<BR>
<I>Safety Series No. 50-SG-QA6</I></A>
</B>
<P>
Requirements and recommendations related to the establishment and
implementation of quality assurance for design of items for a
nuclear power plant. Includes all constituent activities of the
project, such as design, manufacture, construction, commissioning
and operations. Applicable to the responsible organization, plant
designers, architect-engineers and, when involved in design
activities, manufacturers, site constructors, plant operators and
other organizations.
<P>
<I>Contents:</I> Introduction; Quality assurance programme
requirements; Design input requirements; Design process planning
and performance; Design interface control; Communication between
design organization and other organizations; Design verification;
Document control; Control of design changes; Corrective action;
Quality assurance records; Audits; Annex I: Typical areas where
procedures for design quality assurance should be dropped; Annex
II: Typical design inputs.
