STI/PUB/612 (46 pp.; 1983)
<BR>
ISBN 92-0-123583-6
<BR>
Price: 180 Austrian Schillings
<P>
<B>
Deep Underground Disposal of Radioactive Wastes: Near-field
Effects
<BR>
<I>Technical Reports Series No. 251</I>
</B>
<P>
This report is part of the IAEA's programme on underground
disposal
of radioactive wastes. The repositories under consideration are
mined cavities in deep continental rocks for the emplacement of
wastes in solid and packaged form. The report further deals with
the effects of heat from high level wastes on the performance of
deep geological repository components. This generation of heat,
which occurs in the near field of the repository system, affects
the mobilization of radionuclides and their subsequent migration
to
the far field. The report mainly deals with high level wastes and
spent fuel, but considers other types of wastes as well, wherever
appropriate.
<P>
<I>Contents:</I> Introduction; Scope; Near-field components;
Near-field effects; Conclusion.
<P>
STI/DOC/10/251 (60 pp., 5 figures; 1985)
<BR>
ISBN 92-0-125385-0
<BR>
Price: 210 Austrian Schillings
<P>
