<A NAME=68>Environmental Assessment Methodologies for Sea Dumping
of
Radioactive Wastes</A>
<BR>
<I>Safety Series No. 65</I>
</B>
<P>
The purpose of this book is to provide guidance and information
on the nature and content of the environmental assessment
required
for permit applications for sea dumping of radioactive wastes.
The
environmental assessment to be submitted by the national
licensing
authority to IMO must first explain the necessity for sea
dumping,
secondly describe the characteristics of the waste and the
dumping,
and thirdly assess the impact of the proposed dumping operation.
This document deals primarily with the scientific and technical
considerations included in environmental assessment documents.
<P>
