STI/PUB/656 (50 pp., 3 figures; 1984)
<BR>
ISBN 92-0-123484-8
<BR>
Price: 190 Austrian Schillings
<P>
<B>
<A NAME=35>Safety Assessment for the Underground Disposal of
Radioactive
Wastes</A>
<BR>
<I>Safety Series No. 56</I>
</B>
<P>
The purpose of the report is to provide guidelines on the
planning, performing and reviewing of safety assessments of
underground radioactive waste repositories. Approaches and areas
to be considered in making such safety assessments are discussed,
the emphasis being placed on repositories for long lived
radioactive wastes in deep geological formations.
<P>
<I>Contents:</I>  Introduction; Objectives and procedures of
safety assessment; Disposal system description; Safety assessment
approach; Scenario analysis; Consequence analysis; Safety
assessment; Glossary; Bibliography.
<P>
STI/PUB/590 (46 pp., 4 figures; 1981)
<BR>
ISBN 92-0-623181-2
<BR>
Price: 150 Austrian Schillings
<P>
<B>
Sediment K<sub>d</sub>s and Concentration Factors for
Radionuclides in the Marine Environment
<BR>
<I>Technical Reports Series No. 247</I>
</B>
<P>
In 1983 new models to calculate dumping rate limits of
radionuclides into the deep sea were adapted. These models
required parameters involving sediment/water interactions. One
such parameter, the sediment/water distribution coefficient
(referred to as K<sub>d</sub> in the deep-ocean environment and
coastal sediment concentration factor in coastal environments),
had only been  measured for a few nuclides.  A new approach for
calculation of these coefficients has been developed, using
stable element  geochemical data. In addition, concentration
factor data for marine biological material have been reviewed and
updated, and emphasis has been placed on field derived data. 
Additional data on coefficients for elements not occurring
naturally are also provided.
<P>
<I>Contents:</I>  Introduction; Sediment/water distribution
coefficients; Concentration factors for biological material.
<P>
STI/DOC/10/247 (73 pp.; 1985)
<BR>
ISBN 92-0-125085-1
<BR>
Price: 240 Austrian Schillings
<P>
<B>
Severe Accidents in Nuclear Power Plants
<BR>
<I>Proceedings Series</I>
</B>
<P>
(See under <A HREF=npp.html#72>Nuclear Power Plants</A>)
